{"id":14881661,"mediaExerciseId":"b00c7523-955a-4f6a-a596-52f4be21a17b","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"19","chapterTitle":"Cash and Liquidity Management","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"19.2","sectionTitle":"Understanding Float","pageNumber":648,"solutions":[{"id":5999080,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"**a)** It is much better and more interesting for the company to reduce the disbursement float. Companies need to control payments and reduce payment costs. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**b)**   The daily average float can be calculated using the following two formulas\n$$\\begin{align*}\n\\text{Average daily float}&=\\frac{\\text{Total float}}{\\text{Total days}}\\\\\n\\end{align*}$$ \nor\n$$\\begin{align*}\n\\text{Average daily float}& =\\text{ Average daily receipts}\\cdot\\text{Weighted average delay}\n\\end{align*}","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**c)**  It is very important to reduce the float to a minimum. That is, make a balance between payments and withdrawals. If a company has more cash than it still needs, it loses the money it could get by investing that money in securities. On the other hand, if the company has less cash than it needs, then it must borrow from the bank and pay for that service. Thus, the benefit of a reduced float is that the firm earns additional revenue and does not affect other cash flows","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/fa37ffbb08e81203f1dea6e1efa09c68/8e24c217647c1048d95dc02024ccb4ee/lateximg_large.png","width":657},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/fa37ffbb08e81203f1dea6e1efa09c68/8e24c217647c1048d95dc02024ccb4ee/lateximg.png","